## Intent

Demonstrate Uganda's existing presence within the South African coffee market.

## Visible Text

### Uganda Already Has Market Presence

Uganda supplied approximately 1.23 million kilograms of green coffee into South Africa during 2024.

Uganda ranked among the leading coffee origins supplying the South African market.

South African buyers already recognise Uganda as a coffee-producing origin.

### Strategic Implication

Market-entry risk is reduced because Uganda is not an unknown supplier.

Statistic:
1.23 Million KG Imported From Uganda

Statistic:
Top 5 Origin Country

Statistic:
~5% Share Of Green Coffee Imports

## Image Brief

Trade corridor visual connecting Uganda coffee production with South African coffee consumption.
